 POLICE in the Federal Capital Territory (FCT) have launched a rescue operation for a Catholic priest abducted on Sunday, spokesman Yusuf Mariam said in a statement on Monday. “The Commissioner of Police FCT CP. Bala Ciroma has launched a manhunt to trail and apprehend the suspects. “While urging residents to be security conscious and promptly report all suspicious movements, the Command wishes to reiterate its unflinching commitment to the protection of lives and property in the Federal Capital Territory,” the statement said.